**Severity:** Critical

**OWASP Top 10 2021 Category:** Broken Access Control

**Description:**

CVE-2014-0160 is a remote code execution vulnerability in Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) web server that allows an attacker to take control of the server by sending a specially crafted HTTP request.

**Impact:**

* Attackers can gain remote control of the web server.
* Attackers can execute arbitrary code on the server.
* Attackers can access sensitive information on the server.

**Solution:**

To fix this issue, apply the following updates from Microsoft:

* **Microsoft Security Bulletin MS14-066:** https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/security-updates/securitybulletins/2014/ms14-066
* **KB3126598 (Update for Microsoft WebDav)**: https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/kb/3126598

**Additional Recommendations:**

* Keep your IIS web server up to date with the latest security patches.
* Restrict access to the web server to authorized users.
* Implement a web application firewall (WAF) to block malicious requests.
* Use a vulnerability scanner to regularly check for vulnerabilities on your web server.
